oakcurric:unit-497
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Nuclear physics"@en ;
  curric:slug "nuclear-physics" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit covers atomic structure, isotopes, radioactive decay, and half-life. It
  explores alpha, beta, and gamma radiation, nuclear fission and fusion, and the uses of
  radiation in medicine, highlighting differences between contamination and irradiation."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupils’ prior learning from Patterns in the periodic
  table, where they explored how atomic structure influences the properties and reactivity of
  elements. It deepens their understanding by examining nuclear physics, including radioactive
  decay and nuclear processes, and how these impact material properties. As the final unit in
  the big question, Why do materials have different properties?, it reinforces how atomic and
  nuclear structures shape the behaviour and characteristics of materials.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-497-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-497-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-497-3 ,
