oakcurric:unit-493
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Electromagnetism"@en ;
  curric:slug "electromagnetism" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit explores magnetism, including permanent and induced magnets, magnetic
  fields, and Earth's magnetism. It covers current-induced magnetic effects, electric
  motors, and devices like microphones and loudspeakers, with an emphasis on models,
  calculations, and practical applications."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupils’ prior learning from Magnets and
  electromagnets, where they explored the basic principles of magnetism and electromagnetic
  fields. It deepens their understanding by examining electromagnetism in more complex
  applications, such as electric motors and generators. As the final unit in the big question,
  How do electricity and magnetism work?, it reinforces pupils’ understanding of the
  interconnected nature of electricity and magnetism and their applications in technology and
  everyday life.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-493-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-493-2 ,
