  container that makes the waves easier to observe."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-09T00:46:04.287753Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-slow-motion
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "slow motion"@en ;
  schema:description """A film played back in slow motion shows everything happening slowly,
  including the speed of a timer shown in the film."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-09T00:46:04.287758Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-wave-equation
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "wave equation"@en ;
  schema:description "The wave equation is: wave speed = frequency × wavelength, v = f × λ."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-09T00:46:04.287783Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-random-motion
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "random motion"@en ;
  schema:description """Describes the movement of particles in a fluid that travels at a range of
  speeds in all directions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-09T00:46:04.287789Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-convection-current
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "convection current"@en ;
  schema:description """The movement of fluids caused by differences in density within the fluid,
  which allows energy to be transferred as the hotter fluid rises to cooler areas."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-09T00:46:04.287793Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-random-error
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "random error"@en ;
  schema:description """Causes results to differ by different amounts due to a factor other than the
  independent variable (the factor we changed)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-09T00:46:04.288089Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-systematic-error
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "systematic error"@en ;
  schema:description """Causes measurements to differ from the true value by the same amount each
  time they are taken."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-09T00:46:04.288094Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-vector
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "vector"@en ;
  schema:description """graphics made up of paths defined by mathematical equations, scalable
  without losing quality"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-09T00:46:04.289185Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-opaque
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "opaque"@en ;
  schema:description "Light cannot pass through objects that are opaque."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-09T00:46:04.289341Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-turbine
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "turbine"@en ;
  schema:description """A turbine is a machine through which liquid or gas flows to turn a
  wheel."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-09T00:46:04.291751Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-electric-shock
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "electric shock"@en ;
  schema:description """An electric shock occurs when electricity passes into our bodies. It can be
  very dangerous."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-09T00:46:04.291778Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-electrical-insulator
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "electrical insulator"@en ;
  schema:description """An electrical insulator is a material that does not allow electricity to
  pass through it easily."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-09T00:46:04.291796Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-object-distance
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "object distance"@en ;
  schema:description "The object distance is the distance between an object and a lens."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-09T00:46:04.291900Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-image-distance
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "image distance"@en ;
  schema:description """The image distance is the distance between a lens and an image formed by
  that lens."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-09T00:46:04.291905Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-principal-focus
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "principal focus"@en ;
  schema:description """The principal focus is the point to which parallel rays (from distant
  objects) are focused."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-09T00:46:04.291910Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keyword-focal-length
  a curric:Keyword ;
  schema:name "focal length"@en ;
  schema:description """The focal length is the distance between the centre of a lens and the
  principal focus."""@en ;
